node.text:
@nickyjam in his latest post was wearing a special @rolex Day-Date ‘Arabic’ in platinum with ice blue dial. The platinum is the most precious material used by Rolex and it is frequently paired with an ice blue dial, made special with arabic calendar and numerals. Introduced in 2016 this model was only available to select dealers in the Middle East, this year Rolex has secretly released the new version in olive green. #Rolex

Retail price: $ 63,200.00
Market price: $ 165,000.00

Photo: @nickyjam | @rolex

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Toronto, Ontario with @champagnepapi, and @patekphilippe. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: That Drake is a Certified Watch Lover is not a secret, this part of collection is worth $2.7 million dollars and are only @patekphilippe watches. We decided to analyze every watch featured in this photo, let’s have a look. The first watch on its left is a Nautilus Chronograph 5980/1R in 18k rose gold, one of the most popular models in the celebrity world ($250,000.00). Moving to the right we find another Nautilus, the 5976/1G chronograph created for the 40th anniversary of this model, the watch is a limited edition of 1300 pieces ($525,000.00). The orange Aquanaut in the center of the five is the first Acquanaut Chronograph 5968A ever produced ($150,000.00), this watch is made in steel and Patek has recently introduced it in 2 white gold versions. The last two remaining are Nautilus 5719 completely covered with brilliant-cut and baguette-cut diamonds, one version in white gold ($500,000.00) and the other in rose gold ($600,000.00). In the pic you can see two other watches, the one on the left is an exclusive Nautilus 5724R in rose gold with baguette-cut bezel and Tiffany & Co stamp on the dial ($400,000.00). The one on the right is a Grand Complication Perpetual Calendar 5271P in platinum ($300,000.00), a classic watch but also set with baguette-cut diamonds on bezel. How much do you think is the total value of Drake's collection? #PatekPhilippe

node.text:
The model @irinashayk wears a @jacobandco Brilliant Flying Tourbillon ‘Tsavorites’ in 18k rose gold, full-set with green tsavorites. The precious stones are meticulously sourced and matched for cut, clarity, quality, and color. The tourbillon is placed at 6 o’clock surrounded by 146 baguette-cut green tsavorites. The case is set with 170 baguette-cut green tsavorites, 14 baguette-cut and 1 cabochon-cut green tsavorite on the crown. #JacobandCo

Limited edition: 18 pieces
Retail price: $600,000.00

Photo : @highsnobiety | @jacobandco

node.text:
@achrafhakimi of Paris Saint-Germain wears a new @rolex Submariner Date 126610LV in stainless steel with green ceramic bezel and black dial. Introduced in 2020 after the famous ‘Hulk’ this watch took the nickname of ‘Cermit’ inspired by the green bezel Submariner ‘Kermit’, made for the 50th anniversary of the model. The latest generation of the iconic Submariner Date features a re-designed case of 41mm with slimmer lugs. #Rolex

Retail price: $9,300.00
Market price: $19,250.00

Photo: @psg | @rolex

node.text:
@platinumtimesco with their new Patek Philippe 6102R Grand Complications Sky Moon Celestial in 18k rose gold, one of the favorite watches owned by Lebron James. The celestial dial features black sapphire-crystal disks for sky background and moon phases, transparent sapphire-crystal disk for sky chart and Milky Way. Through this watch you can see the exact configuration of the nocturnal sky in the northern hemisphere, with the apparent movement of the stars and the phases and orbit of the moon. #PatekPhilippe

Photo: @platinumtimesco

node.text:
The actor @simuliu, star of new movie ‘Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings’ during the 2021 Met Gala was wearing a @jacobandco Astronomia Solar in 18k white gold. The base and the lugs are set with a total of 382 baguette-cut diamonds. The case of the astronomia allows you to admire four planets from the solar system, an hand-painted blue magnesium globe for Planet Earth and three gemstones crafted in the most complex of cuts: an amethyst, a garnet and a smoked quartz stone. #JacobandCo

Limited edition: 18 pieces
Retail price: $ 780,000.00

Photo: @gettyimages | @jacobandco

node.text:
Frank Ocean attended the 2021 Met Gala wearing a @richardmille RM 37-01 Automatic Kiwi, one of the limited-edition watches part of the Bonbon collection. The front bezels of the RM 37-01 Kiwi is made from Carbon TPT® and the caseback is made from green Quartz TPT®. The caseband uses a gradient of Carbon TPT® /green Quartz TPT®, creating an elegant colour transition from the bezel to the caseback. Each candy is painted with acrylic paint and lacquered by hand with some sugar effect. #RichardMille

Limited edition: 30 pieces
Retail price: $ 138,000.00

Photo: @gettyimages | @richardmille

location.name: The Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY on September 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
We’ve picked up 5 of the best watches worn during the 2021 F1 Grand Prix of Italy, from the classiest Patek Philippe to the latest releases of Richard Mille.

Andrea Pirlo | Patek Philippe
The football legend was wearing a @patekphilippe Annual Calendar 4947/1A in stainless steel. Introduced in 2021 is equipped with a new integrated bracelet featuring five rows of links and an elegant midnight blue dial enhanced by a double vertical and horizontal satin finish.
Retail price: $ 47,900.00

Felipe Massa | Richard Mille
The former Scuderia Ferrari racer which is one of the first RM ambassadors wears a @richardmille RM 65-01 Automatic Winding Split-seconds Chronograph made in Carbon TPT®, one of the most complex RM timepieces ever made.
Retail price: $ 310,000.00

Usain Bolt | Hublot
The fastest man ever rocks a @hublot Spirit of Big Bang Black Magic made in ceramic. This timepiece is one of the signature pieces of the brand and it features a chronograph skeleton caliber.
Retail price: $ 26,200.00

Jean Todt | Patek Philippe
The FIA boss and watch collector wears a classic @patekphilippe Annual Calendar Chronograph 5960P. This watch was released in 2006 as the first in-house chronograph movement, it features a platinum case paired with a grey dial.
Retail price: $ 92,700.00

Lando Norris | Richard Mille 
Second placed of McLaren Team celebrated with a @richardmille RM 35-01 ‘Rafael Nadal’ made in ultralight carbon TPT®. The English driver used to wear an RM 67-02 ‘Mclaren’ but unfortunately got robbed during the UEFA European Championship final at Wembley stadium.
Retail price: $ 125,000.00

Photo: @andreapirlo21 | @kymillman | @gettyimages | @usainbolt

Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Flushing Meadows, New York with @medwed33, and @bovet1822. May be an image of 1 person and wrist watch.

node.text:
@medwed33 wins an historic 2021 US Open Final in three sets against the World Number 1 @djokernole. The Russian tennis champion celebrated the win wearing his @bovet1822 Flying Tourbillon OttantaSei (86 in Italian) designed in collaboration with Pininfarina, one of the most famous car designer. Four sapphire crystals around the 44 mm diameter of the watch allow for the movement to be viewed at every dimension. The tourbillon’s architecture and design increase both the piece’s accuracy and transparency, since its attachments are practically invisible. #Bovet

Limited edition: 86 pieces
Retail price: $ 207,000.00

Photo: @usopen | @bovet1822
